    helper=
        `
       Discord already introduces new members, but you can always make it better!
       Add a custom message to your new members, and optionally let me send a special image to introduce them~ 

       You can make even prettier welcome messages using my <a target="blank" href="/embedarchitect">Embed Architect Tool</a>, so you can incorporate embeds, images, user level, and much more!
        <b>Here's a cheatsheet of dynamic values you can add:</b>
        <table>
        <tr><th>Alias</th><th>Item</th></tr>
        <tr><td class="cheatsheet_comm"> %username% </td>  <td>  Username  </td> </tr>
        <tr><td class="cheatsheet_comm"> %tag% </td>  <td>  Username#0000  </td> </tr>
        <tr><td class="cheatsheet_comm"> %userid% </td>  <td>  User ID  </td> </tr>
        <tr><td class="cheatsheet_comm"> %user% / %mention% </td>  <td> @User  </td> </tr>
        <tr><td class="cheatsheet_comm"> %userBackground% </td>  <td>  Equipped Pollux Background  </td> </tr>
        <tr><td class="cheatsheet_comm"> %reputation% </td>  <td>  Public Reputation (Commend)  </td> </tr>
        <tr><td class="cheatsheet_comm"> %lvGlobal% </td>  <td>  User Global Level  </td> </tr>
        <tr><td class="cheatsheet_comm"> %pfLink% </td>  <td>  User Profile Link  </td> </tr>
        <tr><td class="cheatsheet_comm"> %server% </td>  <td> Server Name  </td> </tr>
        <tr><td class="cheatsheet_comm"> %membernumber% </td>  <td>  Server Member Count  </td> </tr>
        <tr><td class="cheatsheet_comm"> %serverIcon% </td>  <td>  Server Icon URL  </td> </tr>
        <tr><td class="cheatsheet_comm"> %userAvatar% </td>  <td>  User Avatar URL  </td> </tr>
        </table>
        <br>
        *If embed color is left blank, the Member's favcolor will be used
        `
